Paper: hep-th/0204173

Date: 2002-04-20

Title: Noncommutative gravity in three dimensions coupled to spinning sources

Authors: Kiyoshi Shiraishi, Kenji Sakamoto and Nahomi Kan (Yamaguchi Univ.)

Comments: 13 pages, 1 eps figure

Noncommutative gravity in three dimensions with vanishing cosmologicalconstant is examined. We find a solution which describes a spacetime in thepresence of a torsional source. We estimate the phase shift for each partialwave of a scalar field in the spacetime by the Born approximation.